rComments: He always give similar examples before the test and get great mark. Take this prof!

Avoid at all cost. Alot harder than the finance class teached by other profs. Puts questions you have never seen before in the quizzes. Very unclear about his grading requirement. You can lose half the points on a question by getting the right answer but writing too much info.
Awful. I'll make sure to not have him ever again. Avoid him!!!!!! So hard compared to all the other finance classes. My friends had it way easier than I did.

Lectures are hard to understand, full of rubbish with very strong accent. 3 tests instead of midterm, you cannot have own cheat sheet for them, his is not useful. Questions are difficult as he like asking what he didnt teach. Other profs have 4 easier tests and can drop the worst one, and allow to write whatever you want on cheat sheet. Avoid him!

Attendance is mandatory. We have 3 tests during the term but don't have the midterm exam. His tests are good and easy to get a high grade if you catch up his teaching. HOWEVER, his final exam is SUPER hard.

Tests were easy. He takes attendance, 3 tests, 40% final. Last chapter was very difficult, but his finals prep was unfair; all sections wrote the same test, but he never covered some of the material that appeared on it (no exaggeration), and all other sections were allowed custom cheat sheets WITH examples while we only received a list of formulas.

Give him a chance! I first had Chen Guo for adm2350 and did not have a good experience. But I took adm3351 with him in 3rd year and he was a changed man! He completely stopped yelling at the class and made complex topics simple to understand. Make sure you do all the in-class and hw exercises and the midterms and final will be very manageable.

He will ask a few questions in class and he will not move on until a student has answered the questions. If no one raises their hand, he really lays it on thick about how participation is key. He takes attendance at every class, if you miss 3 or so, he refuses to give final exams. His tests are exactly like his practice questions though.
if you show up to his review class you will have no problem getting a good grade

Prof Guo is an amazing prof! I took 2350 and 3351 with him and got A+ in both courses. If you actually assist to al his lectures, he will teach you so many financial world knowledge that cannot be learn through a textbook. His exams HIGHLY reflect what the class exercises, so attend his classes!!

Underrated prof. His powerpoints are all you need to do well in the course. His tests reflect the homework questions assigned. Attendance is mandatory (takes up quite a bit of time doing roll-call). You can definitely do well in his class if you try. Those powerpoints will be your new best friend.

He s a funny guy. Quizzes are like past years, his formula sheet s very useful. The textbook s useless, and I spent 160 bucks on it. Read his ppt, it helped a lot. The final was tricky tho. I would say he did a good job. tbh, I didn't reallystudy but still got a B+, so TAKE HIM!

If you do your discussion group questionshomework to prepare for your quizzes and for your exams, you will be fine. Professor Guo is somewhat hard to understand with his accents. I find his lectures are long and the powerpoints are not very useful. The prof is willing to clarify and help. Also, his formula sheets will save the day! Takes up qs.
Professor Guo is somewhat hard to understand but is always willing to clarify and help when needed. The tests are very fair, final was a bit tricky.

The quizzes are tough and often go beyond what was studied in class or in the practice problems so you need to really work hard to do well. Midterm and final are very similar to the quizzes. His formula sheet is great and detailed. Lectures are long and confusing but his ppt is all you need to do well. Takes up hw questions in class which is nice

Chen is a wildcard. You can study the same amount for two different quizzes and get an A on one and fail the other. Spends 20% of the lectures taking attendance and those brief couple of seconds before your name gets called is as close to excitement and intrigue as you are going to get in his class.

Had him for Fixed Income Investments. Great in-class reviews before midtermsexam. No surprises, just do a lot of practice problems and you'll do fine. He has a lot of knowledge of the subject matter and can be quite funny! Did not use the textbook at all... don't bother buying it seriously. His notes are so detailed.
Funny guy.

Really good prof! It's hard to understand him at first but you get used to it throughout the first few weeks of class! His mid-terms are pretty easy; there are no surprises and if you go to class you shouldn't have any problem! His final is a bit more tricky but still fair! Overall good prof!

Amazing prof, best finance one I've had. Explains basic concepts thoroughly so the noobs understand and relates it all to real-world situations. Highly recommended, not sure why anyone would dislike this professor, his accent is not even bad!

He's actually a pretty decent prof. His lecture notes, or lecture documents, are very detailed and very helpful. I didn't need to buy the textbook. He explained everything multiple times in class. The midterms and exam were all fair and there were no surprises. He's a nice guy
Very hard to understand, somewhat helpful during office hours, but come to class prepared or you will have a hard time following
Very nice guy, but not the best prof.

Amazing. You know what he expects. Just do the homework from the start. Stay on track and start the project early. Read chapters before class and you'll understand better.  He can be really clear if you ask questions. He wants you to pass... with good study time you can get an A. If you hate finance then switch to arts. the building is still close.

Oh lord, one on one his english is good but in class it's incomprehensible. On a good day there will be 20-25 students out of 50-60. He just reads everything off the slides so if you go to class or not it doesn't matter. I liked this course but after attending this class I just want to pass it and get it over with.

Lectures are deathly boring.  He is very disorganized.  Midterm is okay.  Final project is tough so start soon.  Final exam is okay though multiple choice is tricky.  Read chapters very closely for the m/c or else you'll bomb it.  Avoid if possible.

Attending class is an utter waste of time.  Total class size of 70 and 15 students show up on a good day.  Does not explain thorougly though the textbook helps for formulating solutions.  Very monotonous style.  Explanations for the project are uselsess so make sure to  ask many direct questions as to what he expects for the project. AVOID HIM.

Horrible!!!! Avoid at all costs!!! Does not give clear instructions on projects and picks marks without anyway to support them. Sitting through class is a waste if time, if you must take this class just teach yourself becase he will not teach you anything. Good luck with the project he picks the groups that do exactly what he says not to do.
Best Finance Professor
His teaching is CRAP, but I dont have any idea how he will mark the papers. This course with him was like a HELL for me
Good!!!
Thanks for nothing. He is crap.
